The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Nov. 10: After rising for five consecutive weeks, rate of inflation fell to 5.09 per cent during the week ended October 28, compared with 5.41 per cent in the previous week with drop in prices of essential commodities. This was the fourth week in a row that wholesale prices-based inflation rate stood above the 5 per cent mark. Inflation stood at 4.75 per cent during the corresponding week of the previous year.

 New Delhi, Nov. 10: Finance minister P. Chidambaram today favoured a close hard look at tax exemptions in a bid to bring fiscal prudence. Along with his budget this year, a paper presented by him indicated that various tax exemptions and incentives cost the exchequer Rs 1,58,000 crore.

 New Delhi, Nov. 11: FIPB is understood to have cleared the proposal from Essar group seeking to restructure the equity of Hutchison Essar today, which takes the foreign shareholding to the permissible limit of 74 per cent.

 Mumbai, Nov. 10: Harrisons Malayalam has got shareholders nod to hive off Kaliyar estate in Kerala for Rs 53 crore through a postal ballot.

 Mumbai, Nov. 10: Market regulator Sebi today dismissed the case against Niskalp Investments and Trading Company, alleged to have manipulated price of Global Trust Bank shares.




